modules.description: Provides functions for managing and manipulating name-spaced identifiers, including prefixing, suffixing, and combining namespaces. Works with strings and custom namespace types to ensure unique identifier resolution. Used to generate unique variable names in code generation pipelines and manage symbol scopes in interpreters.

Generates OCaml modules from directory structures, mapping files to module paths and handling lex/yacc files. Processes `.ml`, `.mli`, and namespace directories, creating module hierarchies based on file system layout. Applies custom filename transformations and integrates with build systems via hooks and file deletion routines.
